{
  "id": "c0c0c0c0-0011-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "name": "Stale Closure Prevention",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1738454400000,
  "modified": 1773243817443,
  "content": {
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Event handlers in Hobson views capture data at render time, but the database may have been updated since then (especially via "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-0010-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "silent updates"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "). Using stale closure data for database writes causes bugs where changes silently revert."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "The Problem"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "JavaScript closures capture variables from their enclosing scope. When a view renders, handlers close over the current item state:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "export async function render(item, api) {\n  const attachments = item.attachments;  // Snapshot at render time\n\n  titlebar.onmousedown = () => {\n    // BUG: Uses stale data! Other windows may have moved since render.\n    const maxZ = Math.max(...attachments.map(c => c.z));\n  };\n}"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "After silent updates (drag, z-index changes), the database holds current state but the closure still has the render-time snapshot. This causes:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Windows jumping to wrong positions"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — stale position data overwrites current positions"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Z-index calculations using old data"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — maxZ computed from stale values"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Position updates reverting other windows"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — writing stale attachment array back"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "The Solution: Always Read Fresh"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "In any event handler that reads or writes item data, fetch the current state from the database:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "titlebar.onmousedown = async () => {\n  const freshItem = await api.get(item.id);  // Current state from DB\n  const freshChildren = freshItem.attachments;\n  const maxZ = Math.max(...freshChildren.map(c => c.z));\n};"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Critical Locations"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Any function that:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ol",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Reads"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " item data and makes decisions based on it"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Writes"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " item data back to the database"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Runs "
            },
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "asynchronously"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " after render time (event handlers, callbacks, timers)"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Must fetch fresh state first. Key examples:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "updateChild()"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — MUST read fresh attachments before modifying"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Click-to-front handler — MUST read fresh z-indices for maxZ"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Drag end handler — MUST read fresh state before saving final position"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Any handler that modifies the parent item's attachments array"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Red Flags"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Watch for these patterns in code review:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Variables captured from outer scope used inside "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "async"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " handlers"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Array/object snapshots used for database writes"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Calculations based on \"current\" data that might be stale"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "item.attachments.map(...)"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " inside an event handler (should be "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "freshItem.attachments.map(...)"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ")"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "The Rule"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":blockquote",
        [
          ":p",
          [
            ":strong",
            {
              "s": "If you're in an event handler and need item data, call `api.get()` first."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The cost is one IndexedDB read (fast, local). The benefit is correctness."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "See Also"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
